mesquite.lib

Class NameReference

  • java.lang.Object
    • mesquite.lib.NameReference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Listable

    public class NameReference
extends java.lang.Object
implements Listable
    A class to hold a string. It is used to speed up string checking. That is, in some circumstances (see ContinuousData) one can obtain a NameReference containing a string giving the name of some object. Then, if one later is checking objects one can ask if its NameReference is the one obtained previously. Before checking that the contained strings are identical, it can check if the NameReferences are identical, thus saving lots of time. Used where some name/string needs to be checked often.
